(
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB4FFE2D08BF8C778EAF8D7" box="[160,226,1881,1907]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1900,1925]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,184,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1430,174,1880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Balala hainana Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. ♂, A–I Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and thorax, lateral view; D. Habitus, ventral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Pygofer, lateral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; I. Connective and style, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, dorsal view. K, L Paratype: K. Pygofer, lateral view; L. Pygofer, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="075836ABFFB4FFE3D0BCF83F7BA3FEC3" blockId="10.[151,1436,1953,2015]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,153,359]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB4FFE2D0BCF83F78E5F81F" bold="true" box="[151,237,1953,1979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Length</emphasis>
(including forewing): 
<specimenCount id="11E1FD22FFB4FFE2D1C0F83F7A08F81F" box="[491,512,1953,1979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<quantity id="C01F9B4EFFB4FFE2D22CF83F7ACFF81F" box="[519,711,1953,1979]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.14" metricValueMax="1.172" metricValueMin="1.108" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="11.4" valueMax="11.72" valueMin="11.08">11.08–11.72 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB4FFE2D0ECF85B79D9F87B" bold="true" box="[199,465,1989,2015]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">External morphology.</emphasis>
Body brownish-red to dark brown. Crown (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB4FFE2D3F2F85B7C3DF87B" box="[985,1077,1989,2015]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1900,1925]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,184,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1430,174,1880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Balala hainana Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. ♂, A–I Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and thorax, lateral view; D. Habitus, ventral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Pygofer, lateral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; I. Connective and style, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, dorsal view. K, L Paratype: K. Pygofer, lateral view; L. Pygofer, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
) anterior margin round, length shorter than 1/2 width between eyes. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB5FFE3D401FF077CA6FF17" box="[1066,1198,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1900,1925]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,184,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1430,174,1880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Balala hainana Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. ♂, A–I Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and thorax, lateral view; D. Habitus, ventral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Pygofer, lateral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; I. Connective and style, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, dorsal view. K, L Paratype: K. Pygofer, lateral view; L. Pygofer, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635596/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Figs. 8A, C</figureCitation>
) truncated well short of clavus, exposed part of mesonotum about 1/6–1/4 scutellum length, scutellum with centre compressed into keel vertically and truncate subapically in lateral view, median longitudinal ridge moderately weak and extended through entire scutellum or not. Forewing with one indistinct transparent band present between apical cells and appendix. Abdomen with pair of continuous yellow patches on 3rd to 5th tergites submedially. Hind femur with 4–5 macrosetae at apex, tibia with ca. 9–10, 12 setae in rows AD, PD, respectively.
</paragraph>
<caption id="53986623FFB5FFE3D0BCF92878C6F8B3" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635592" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3635592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635592/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" startId="11.[151,250,1718,1743]" targetBox="[179,1400,384,1687]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph id="075836ABFFB5FFE3D0BCF92878C6F8B3" blockId="11.[151,1436,1718,1815]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB5FFE3D0BCF928791AF96B" bold="true" box="[151,274,1718,1743]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C0E74D28FFB5FFE3D133F9287A48F96B" authority="Tang &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Tang &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2020" box="[280,576,1718,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujiana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB5FFE3D133F92879A1F96A" box="[280,425,1718,1742]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Balala fujiana</emphasis>
Tang &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB5FFE3D26EF9297A9DF96B" bold="true" box="[581,661,1719,1743]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EA057C2FFB5FFE3D26EF9297A9DF96B" box="[581,661,1719,1743]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
♂, A–E Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D. Face; E. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view. F, G. Paratypes: Habitus, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="075836ABFFB5FFE3D0ECF8DB7CEBF84B" blockId="11.[151,1437,1860,2031]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB5FFE3D0ECF8DB7970F8FB" bold="true" box="[199,376,1860,1887]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB5FFE3D1CEF8DB7A38F8FB" box="[485,560,1861,1887]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1900,1925]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,184,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1430,174,1880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Balala hainana Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. ♂, A–I Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and thorax, lateral view; D. Habitus, ventral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Pygofer, lateral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; I. Connective and style, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, dorsal view. K, L Paratype: K. Pygofer, lateral view; L. Pygofer, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635596/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
E–G, L, K) with dorsal inner margin nearly straight, subapex of ventral margin round or a little angulate, many small short setae arranged along ventral margin; ventral appendage approaching or even reaching apex of pygofer, gradually curved dorsad. Subgenital plate about as long as 1/2 pygofer side. Apical margin of connective (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB5FFE3D1BEF82F79E9F86F" box="[405,481,1969,1995]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1900,1925]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,184,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1430,174,1880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Balala hainana Tang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. ♂, A–I Holotype: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and thorax, lateral view; D. Habitus, ventral view; E. Pygofer, dorsal view; F. Pygofer, ventral view; G. Pygofer, lateral view; H. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; I. Connective and style, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, dorsal view. K, L Paratype: K. Pygofer, lateral view; L. Pygofer, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635596/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="34">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
H–J) nearly straight; style about 1.5x longer than connective; aedeagus shaft tubular, apical half of dorsal surface rugulose, preatrium slightly longer than shaft, gonopore at shaft apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
